items.name: Krueger Caricature art style XL v1.0
items.description:
Introducing the Sebastian Kr√ºger Art Style for SDXL 1.0

Experience the iconic artistry of Sebastian Kr√ºger, a renowned German artist celebrated for his captivating caricatures and hyperrealistic portraits. Kr√ºger's distinctive approach involves skillfully exaggerating details in his depictions of celebrities, capturing their essence while infusing a touch of surrealism. By manipulating proportions and expressions with finesse, he crafts larger-than-life interpretations that both celebrate and satirize his subjects, often drawn from the vibrant realm of pop culture.

The artistic journey, however, isn't without its challenges.Diffusers obviously can't understand a persons personality and to create a caricature becomes a task of trial and error combined with prompting and seed surfing.

This version 1.0, represents my initial exploration into the realm of training a LORA. While it might not be flawless, I hope it offers an enjoyable outlet for personal amusement.

In my usage, I've found a weight of approximately 1 to be effective, although you may need to fine-tune it based on prompt complexity. A clip skip value of 1 was applied to the images shared on this page, and mostly CFG 7 normallly gave me decent results.

The main trigger word is kru3ger_style. As I continue to explore the capabilities of this Lora, I invite you to review the prompts I've used for the images I've posted. Additionally, your contributions and prompts shared here will provide valuable insights into effective interactions.

Personally in my testing i get good results for portraits with 3:4 ratio (1024*1365). I will post 3 example images with the same prompt & seed in this gallery to demonstrate the difference it makes in style when used with that aspect ratio,(1) with and (2) without trigger word, (3) one vanilla one

It's important to note that my creation of this Lora was fueled purely by admiration, devoid of any commercial intent. For those captivated by this unique art style, I encourage you to explore Sebastian Kr√ºger's official channels and consider acquiring pieces from this remarkable artist.

If you're brimming with ideas for future projects, I welcome your input! Dive into the enchanting realm of this remarkable technology, experiment with its potential, and remember to share your outstanding creations for all to enjoy.

Your feedback is invaluable, so if you find this tool beneficial, don't hesitate to leave a review and showcase your captivating works of art!

items.name: ‚ãÖ ‚ä£ Realities Edge XL ‚ä¢ ‚ãÖ
items.description:
• V.4 is up! Better photorealism...AGAIN!

  • V.3 wants DPM+ 3M SDE and V3 also has a new better license!

  • Image compatibility between COMFYUI and A1111 - same image everywhere! This breaks seeds and you will not be able to get same image as me without these changes! Read more here: https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet/discussions/2039

‚Üì Settings and recommendations down below ‚Üì

-|- VAE is needed, this one: https://civitai.com/api/download/models/126601?type=VAE&format=Other

Easy and complex at the same time, this model is very versatile in the right hands. Better photorealism in XL is here.

‚ãÖ ‚ä£ Why?

Look no further. The era of sharp versatile models for XL is here, in big part because of this awesome community. This is a model accumulating upon the knowledge provided by the SDXL 1.0 model and the incredible base it has given us - thanks to the team over at StabilityAI!

But as many have noted, there is always room for improvement. This model aims to take XL generations to a new plateau on which to build further and generate some really cool images along the way - be it photographs or digital art.

Realities Edge (RE) stabilizes some of the weakest spots of SDXL 1.0 base, namely details and lack of texture. Sometimes XL base produced patches of blurriness mixed with in focus parts and to add, thin people and a little bit skewed anatomy. The diversity and range of faces and ethnicities also left a lot to be desired but is a great leap forward since the days of 1.5. Lastly, the art in all its different styles and forms. SDXL base is far more capable than it's predecessors and a huge upgrade for us to play with, but there is some art styles the model still struggles with. The additions made to RE in this regard is big.

SDXL was released to all of us here. Now we build.

‚ãÖ ‚ä£ What?

A methodical chaoswarp* of the best available models on Civitai combined with custom, unreleased, XL Loras I've been training these past weeks have resulted in this model. It is capable of photorealism and natural photography but that just scratches the surface. RE can do NSFW and has great anatomy information paired with Loras for better skin-texture and more realistic faces, eyes and mouths. The hole slew of anatomical corrections have been mostly fixed for the ladies and hands have also improved a lot giving way to staggering realism. The men still have room for improvements, but with this as a base I think that improvement will be here quick.


Realities Edge is first and foremost an art machine. Bombastic oil paintings, atmospheric art photography, futuristic 3D, all forms of digital art and anything in-between. If it's been expressed in art in some period of the human history, RE should be able to handle it or at least give you a great base to train your own stuff with! Loras are more accessible than ever with SDXL being the easiest plattform to train on (but a hard one to master üòâ).

RE has a wide array of art-styles to choose from and most of them come out sharp and vibrant ready for further tweaking if and upscaling if needed. Illustrations, vector, oil paintings, watercolor, vintage cameras like Kodak and Ektachrome; product photography, concept art, macro, portraits, animals, comics, characters, Western-style, Eastern-style, medieval, RPGs like D&D, mechanical parts, aliens and all of these can be combined, twisted around, merged and re-synthesized into whatever concoction you can imagine.

‚ãÖ ‚ä£ How?

Leaning heavily on the fantastic community model maker socalguitarist 's XL models infused with high volumes of my own acidic Loras burning off bad quality, low resolution, wonky eyes and airbrushed skin texture and adding a needed boost to creativity and range of style that the base model from StabilityAI lacks. Together with the training of the community merged within, this model shines.

There have been around 17 iterations before arriving at this one. Models have been merged with regular Checkpoint merging in both Weighted sum and Add difference but the heavy lifting was done in MBW (block merging). The many Loras were trained with Kohyaa-ss with dim rank of 256 for the sharpest detail and highest quality possible, at the cost of diskspace.

Speaking of which. Total footprint for model is ~170GB.

The model is capable of producing some basic anime, but don't despair, during the process there was an anime Lora born from the potion mixing- scheduled for release at the end of August. But that's for another post.

NO REFINER NEEDED

‚ãÖ ‚ä£ Capabilities and recommendations:

  • Photorealism, 3D, 2.5D, Illustrations, Photomanipulation, Portraits and much more

  • NSFW capabilities

  • Works very well with Loras - both as a base to train on and for rendering

  • Excels at both types of CLIP prompting. Be it maximalist OpenAI style prompts or minimalist story driven LAION prompts (written in a more natural language without constant commas).

  • Great lighting and shines with easy short prompts and aggressive (but short) negative prompts.

  • Very low risk of burned generations even on higher CFG - recommend 5.5-15

  • Responds amazingly to hires.fix with just a scaling of 1.0-1.5 and beyond. I like doing it with no scaling at all, but just letting it run through with a sharp upscaler and less steps. If you have the VRAM for it, push the scaling higher, go nuts!

  • Favorite resolution ranges are 768x1344 and 1024x1296. Works good for landscapes on even bigger resolutions. Also works with anamorphic lenses in resolutions of 1920x816 or the likes. Test what works best for you.

  • DPM+ 3M SDE Karras recommended but always test your favorite!

  • All the img2img modes work really well and balancing a low CFG with a higher-than-average Denoising Strength will produce a sharp and clear upscale full of interesting details, using regular SD upscale. I wonder what you can do with Ultimate SD upscale?

  • Likes Clip Skip 1-4. I frequently use 2.

  • Knows about some celebrities - good LoRA base!

  • Use with ToMe (token merging) in A1111 (I'm sure it's implemented in Comfy as well) for a much faster SDXL generation time - changes seeds though!

* = The word "chaoswarp" is defined by large amounts of coffee and lots of nights spent waiting by the computer dreaming up ever more complex prompts, folding styles, tales and characters into elaborate images. After careful block-merging:

  • Images are less saturated as a base (better realism) and with a more somber tone.

  • Took back composition blocks from 2.0 to get better coherency in group images.

  • Kept 3.0 in some blocks since it is more creative.

modelVersions.name: ‚òØÔ∏è‚òØÔ∏è‚òØÔ∏è (3.0)
modelVersions.description:
First, I've changed my A1111 to produce the same images across all different GPUs and ComfyUI (and others). The change implements the official "noise pattern" of Stability AI. This is a seed-breaking change but moving forward is the only way, and this change is sort of "preferred" even by Stability AI themselves. This makes interoperability between different UIs much easier and we can all benefit! This does not mean you can't produce images the old way, but if you want to be able to reproduce my images exactly, you need to change some settings in A1111.
Read here how to do it: https://github.com/Mikubill/sd-webui-controlnet/discussions/2039

MAJOR OVERHAUL:

  • Even easier to prompt to get high quality. DON'T use the old style prompting with 200+ tokens, you'll get a worse image.

  • Let the algo do its thing - CFG at 2-10 but recommend 4.

  • Hands, feet and ears+eyes are now better as well as hair realism. Use your prompting to get what you need!

  • SHARPNESS! <---- Even if RE 2.0 was more sharp than anything else on Civitai I still felt it could be better. 3.0 is a great step in that direction and sharpness is not not only in eyes/photos but in environments as well as in art!

  • The mission statement of Realities Edge is to take photorealism to the next level BUT keeping the model creative and able to create art/3D/NPR images as well - I can finally say with 3.0 that this has been achieved. Unparalleled photorealism but with the "flick" of a prompt, can become something entirely different.

  • Better NSFW. Males are still a hit and miss but there are LORAs (not mine) here on Civit that can help you in that direction if you need it!

To-do:

  • Nipples have a tendency to show up here and there even on clothing - use "nipples" in negative to get that out of the picture!

modelVersions.name: ‚öõÔ∏è‚öõÔ∏è (2.0)
modelVersions.description:
The reVolution continues:

  • Better coherence in natural language prompts

  • Easier prompting and less need for negatives!

  • Sharper in some images, softer in others - detail is preserved in both cases though

  • Even better hands

  • More diverse ethnicities and less prone to creating Asian looking people by default (still works great when prompted for of course)

  • Filmic grain and LUT added when prompted for it

  • Much better NSFW resulting in even more natural pictures even when clothed!

  • Merged Noise Offset Lora from StabilityAI resulting in better contrast - just prompt it away if you need faded/washed out/pastel/vintage color palette!

items.name: SDXL img2img (automatic aspect ratio) | ComfyUI workflow
items.description:
SDXL has recommended aspect ratios it was trained on. Results will be better if you pass correct values into the CLIP. Objects will tend to stay in frame.

This workflow automates this process. You can choose to crop or not to crop, and it will handle the rest.

How it works

If you choose to crop: image will be resized into closest recommended resolution.

If you choose not to crop: image will stay at the same size, but CLIP will get width and height of closest recommended resolution to make an optimal conditioning.

Installation and dependencies

  1. Install WAS Node Suite custom nodes;

  2. Download and open this workflow.

Check out my other workflows

items.name: SDXL FaeTastic
items.description:
Don't use a refiner with this model! Read About Version for changes.

I've been working on this model for the past couple of weeks and felt like I got it to a point where I'd be happy to release it. I've tried to create a model that has the colors and creativity of 1.5 FaeTastic and also tried to fix some issues that I feel SDXL has. I can't promise that it's perfect, but I feel like it's a step in the right direction.

I've trained several LoRAs that haven't been released for the purpose of merging them into the model, and I'll talk about the model genetics below. Hopefully openly talking about the way I merge and create models/LoRAs will open the door for others to learn as well. :)

Because I believe in the open-source spirit of SD, anyone is free to use this model or any of my LoRAs to merge or use as they see fit in an open-source sense, including selling any images or using them in personal projects. I would be extremely grateful to be credited for any merges or uses of my resources.

However, I am very opposed to having my model and resources I personally train and test and spend hundreds of hours on, be put up on third-party generation sites for their monetary gain where I receive nothing in return.

Model Genetics

Everything was merged with SuperMerger in A1111. All LoRAs were trained with Kohya.

  1. Dreamshaper XL .5 with Rundiffusion XL .5

  2. Added on top of that is the Fae Style SDXL LoRA

  3. FaeTastic V1 SDXL .7 with ProtoVisionXL .3

  4. Added SDXL High Details LoRA

  5. Added SDXL Better Eyes LoRA

  6. Trained a FaeTastic SDXL LoRA on high aesthetic, highly detailed, high resolution 1.5 personal generated images and merged in. This LoRA is pretty awesome, and I'll probably release it on its own as well.

  7. Trained an SDXL LoRA on high-resolution, highly detailed images of realistic, drawn, and digital art of hands. These images were up close pictures of hands as well as images of people holding objects. This was merged in.

Recommended Resources

For those interested in training SDXL LoRAs I highly recommend this guide that Ally and I collaborated on together with a lot of extensive testing and training: https://civitai.notion.site/SDXL-1-0-Training-Overview-4fb03d5b4cbf482ebe13ffef7bcb8ead

If you ever have any questions or need help with my resources or anything Civitai related, I am always happy to assist, you can find me in the Civitai discord! <3

modelVersions.name: v1.6
modelVersions.description:
Spent a lot of time testing and fixing the initial FaeTastic SDXL model....skipped a bunch of iterations and decided on the 6th one for this release. ü•≤

  • Trained a ton of hand LoRAs, I would consider it a bit better now at hands. Obviously, monstrosities can appear still, but can more consistently get good ones.

  • Trained a brand new Details LoRA that focused on realism and lighting.

  • FaeTastic Details should be pretty much removed, so you're able to actually use my LoRA with this model now if you prefer more of the cartoon look or just want added colors/details.

  • The model is way more stable than the first iteration, noticed that some LoRAs were causing artifacts...shouldn't do that anymore.

The only negative I would say is that I feel like it's lost a tiny bit of creativity and kinda lost the unique cartoon faces look. The first model is still available to those who prefer that look. I'm going to keep tweaking this consistently though as I love SDXL and am pretty committed to continuous SDXL resource content.

For my next update I think I'm gonna actually finetune it instead of training LoRAs and merging in. I think this way is probably safer to make sure the model is stable.

items.name: Marl Barrock (Reincarnation Colosseum | Tensei Colosseum) | LoCon
items.description:
Marl Barrock from Reincarnation Colosseum an Ecchi/Erotica Manga. Works best on 0.8-1.0. Training done on NAI.

This is a LoCon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5+ so make sure to update otherwise place in Lycoris folder.

Trigger: "MarleBarrock, dark-skinned female" always needed, for accuracy add "Muscular, large breasts" also yes there is a small typo in the trigger but I only noticed after making this post, oops.

Suggestions:

  • Outfit from the Manga "muscular, bandages, bandaged arm, detached sleeves, bandaged legs, black thighhighs, pelvic curtain, tabard".

    • Even "from behind" works ok given the 2-3 back pics ;)

  • Iconic face: "smile, sharp teeth, grin"

  • Hair is very stable but may rarely lose the yellow color on the single bang, just regen at 1.0 weight and it will return.

  • Her outfit loves to bleed into other clothes but many clothes that do not resemble tabards/suits work pretty well.

    • Things like "sideboob, side cutout, tabard" can help counter some of the outfit bleed.

My goal was to improve upon existing LoRAs for this character by getting the look right while having less/no style baked in so it can be used on more models successfully. I manually edited the dataset to cleanup the images and I used Regularization images to achieve a more stable look with less style burn in.

I bumped into this Manga by chance once I for sure wanted to make her once I found out there were colored pictures out there. I got the hair + single bang working very well and consistent even with a 50% black & white dataset. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

items.name: Liber Novus
items.description:
"Liber Novus", commonly referred to as "The Red Book", is a luminous work by the Swiss psychiatrist Carl Jung. It is an exploration of his deepest thoughts, fantasies, and dreams. Illustrated with ornate and profound artwork, this masterwork not only offers insights into the mind of one of the most influential thinkers of the 20th century but also delves deep into the collective unconscious and the nature of the self.

The "Liber Novus" model, named in homage to this magnum opus, seeks to harness the depth and beauty found within "The Red Book" and distill it into a contemporary, inspired format. It's an endeavor that marries the ancient with the modern, the symbolic with the practical, and the mystical with the tangible.

Drawing upon the rich symbolism and intricate illustrations of the original work, the model aims to offer a framework that is both holistic and transformative. Just as Jung ventured into the depths of his psyche to produce "The Red Book", the "Liber Novus" model encourages individuals or entities to embark on their journeys of self-discovery and integration.

[Development]

I am working to craft a high-resolution rendition of this model, merging its authentic symbolism with a contemporary style saturated with vibrant shades. The images presented illuminate the advancements I've achieved to this point. I actively encourage and welcome everyone to share their insights, innovations, and contributions. Your collaboration will be instrumental in realizing the full potential of this model.
